<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Homeowners are today expected to start scrambling to grab a share of the government cash available for green home improvements.</p>

<p>The Green Homes Grant scheme offers up to £5,000 towards energy efficiency improvements that could cut bills by up to £600 a year.</p>

<p>The scheme, which opens for applications today, provides a voucher that covers two thirds of qualifying work to your home. </p>

<p>The Government’s Green Homes Grant scheme offers up to £5,000 towards energy efficiency improvements that could cut bills by up to £600 a year</p>

<p>This could include insulation or installing low-carbon heating. The maximum value of the voucher is £5,000, or £10,000 if you are on a low- income and receive certain benefits.</p>

<p>You must own your own home in England or be a landlord — although landlords can only receive up to £5,000.</p>

<p>You must redeem the voucher and ensure improvements are completed by March 31.</p>

<p>For more information visit gov.uk/guidance/apply-for-the-green-homes-grant-scheme.</p>

